A tire measures 20 inches in diameter. How many revolutions will the tire have completed when it has traveled 100 yards? Express your answer to the nearest whole number.

}

\textbf{Answer:} A tire with a diameter of 20 inches will travel $20\pi$ inches in one revolution. One hundred yards is $100 \times 36 = 3600$ inches. The tire will have to complete about $3600 \div 20\pi \approx \boxed{57\text{ revolutions}}$.
}
